Major: A huge monster in the form of a snail.
Mejaa: Katatsumuri no you na sugata no kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A person with the head and fingers of a gecko.
Mejaa: Yamori no you na atama to yubi wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a gecko.
Mejaa: Yamori no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny shelled reptile that lives in the desert.
A reptile person with the head and tail of a desert tortoise.
Mejaa: Sabaku kame no atama to o wo motsu hachuu ruijin da.
Kyodai sabaku kame no yousei no

Major: A large monster in the form of a desert tortoise.
Mejaa: Sabaku kame no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.
Doku wo motta chiisana tokage da. .
Joukika shita Doku tokage no dokueki

Major: A venomous person with the head and tail of a gila monster.
Mejaa: Doku tokage no atama to shippo wo motsu dokusei ningen da.

Major: A huge beast in the form of a gila monster.
Mejaa: Doku tokage no you na sugata wo shita kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized highly social mammalian carnivore.  It has a keen sense of smell.  It can be trained to obey commands.
Mejaa: Chuugata de shakaisei no tsuyoi, nikushoku honyuurui da. Nioi ni binkan de, choukyou suru koto ga dekiru.

Major: A small mammalian carnivore.  It is usually domestic and hunts vermin.
Mejaa: Chiisana nikushoku honyuurui. Petto to nari, gaichuu wo tsukamaeru.

Major: A compact offspring of horse and donkey, bred to be a beast of burden.
Mejaa: Uma to roba no ainoko de, nimotsu hakobi no kachiku ni naru.

Major: A medium-Sized, hooved herbivore.  Some are domesticated as beasts of burden.
Mejaa: Chuugata no soushoku doubutsu. Nimotsu hakobi no kachiku ni dekiru.

Major: A large hooved, maned herbivore.  They can run swiftly and many are domesticated as steeds.
Mejaa: Hizume no aru oogata soushoku doubutsu. Kachiku ni shite,nin wo nosete hayaku kakeru koto ga dekiru.

Major: A large mammalian herbivore.  They often bear large horns and the males are ill-Tempered.  They are domesticated for milk and meat.
Mejaa: Oogata no soushoku honyuurui. Osu wa ookina kado wo mochi, kishou ga arai. Miruku to niku wo toru tame no kachiku ni dekiru.

Major: A medium-Sized herding animal.  It is prized for its thick wool coat.
Mejaa: Chuugata no soushoku doubutsu. Kachiku ni deki, tokuni youmou wa kachi ga takai.

Major: A medium-Sized domestic animal.  It has a distinctive snout and corkscrew tail.  It is thought by some to be intelligent.
Mejaa: Chuugata no kachiku. Dokutoku na katachi no hana to makibane no you na katachi no o wo motsu. Mare ni kashikoi kotai mo iru.

Major: A medium-Sized herding animal.  It is known for its short horns and beard.
Mejaa: A chuugata no soushoku doubutsu. Mijikai kado to agohige ga tokuchou.

Major: A small domestic bird capable of flying short distances.  It is prized for its tasty eggs.
Mejaa: Mijikai kyori wo tobu koto ga dekiru kakin. Tamago ga oishii.

Major: A small water bird.  It has a long neck and powerful legs meant for swimming and diving.
Mejaa: Chiisana mizutori. Kubi ga nagaku, oyogi ga umai.

Major: A large mammalian herbivore.  It is powerfully built and has long curved horns.
Mejaa: Oogata soushoku honyuurui. Chikara ga totemo tsuyoku, nagakute magatta kado wo motsu.

Major: A large mammalian herbivore living in cold climates.  It has large antlers and sought-After fur.
Mejaa: A large mammalian herbivore living in cold climates.  It has large kaku s and sought-After fusafusa.

Major: A large mammalian herbivore.  It has long fur and curving horns.  It can be found in the mountains.
Mejaa: Nagai ke to magatta kado wo motsu oogata soushoku honyuurui. Sangaku ni seisoku.

Major: A large domestic animal with a long neck.  It has been bred for its valuable hair.
Mejaa: Kubi no nagai oogata soushoku honyuurui. Nagai ke no tame ni shiiku sarete iru.
Rama wo chiisaku shita you na sugata

Major: A small ground-Dwelling bird.  It has a featherless head and eats seeds and insects.  It moves about in groups.
Mejaa: Zenchou 50 senchi hodo no chijou ni sumu tori da. Atama ni ke ga nai no ga tokuchou. Mure wo tsukuri, konchuu ya shokubutsu wo taberu.

Major: A small forest bird.  The male'S tail creates an extravagant display for females.  At night, they roost in the trees.
Mejaa: Mori ni seisoku suru tori. Osu no oha wa, mesu wo hikitsukeru tame ni totemo hade de utsukushii iroai wo shite iru.

Major: A small forest bird known for the distinctive flaps of skin hanging from its face.  It is prized for its meat.
Mejaa: Mori ni sumu chihyousei no tori. Kao kara burasagaru dokutoku no niku bou ga tokuchou. Niku no kachi ga takai.
Nana men tori no hina no

Major: A small lagomorph with long ears.  It has powerful hind legs which it uses to swiftly avoid predators.  It can be found anywhere from forests to deserts.
Mejaa: Mimi no nagai chiisana honyuurui. Ushiroashi ga ookiku, teki kara subayaku nigeru no ni tsukawareru. Mori kara sabaku made, samazama na kikou ni seisoku.

Major: A rolling platform for carrying passengers or cargo.
Mejaa: Joukyaku ya nimotsu wo hakobu tame no kasha.

Major: A tiny flying insect found around rotting meat and garbage.  These bugs are widely considered to be a nuisance.
Mejaa: Gomi ya kusatta niku no mawari ni waku, chiisana sora tobu konchuu. Fukai gaichuu.

Major: A person with the wings and head of a fly.
Mejaa: Hae no atama to tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a fly.
Mejaa: Hae no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small insect that seeks out unwatched food and garbage.  They fear light.
Mejaa: Tabemono ya gomi wo sagasu chiisana gaichuu. Hikari kara nigeru shuusei ga aru.

Major: A person with the wings and head of a roach.
Mejaa: Gokiburi no atama to tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a roach.
Mejaa: Gokiburi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny insect that can be found almost anywhere outside.
Mejaa: Yagai no doko ni de mo iru chiisana konchuu da.

Major: A person with the carapace and head of a beetle.
Mejaa: Kouchuu no atama to koukaku wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a beetle.
Mejaa: Kouchuu no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: This tiny insect can be found in huge colonies in the dirt.  They overwhelm their enemies with swarms.  Some have poison bites.
Mejaa: Tsuchi no naka ni kyodai na su wo tsukuru chiisana konchuu. Mure de teki wo osoi, doku wo motsu shu mo iru.

Major: A small insect with large orange wings.  It is admired for its beauty.
Mejaa: Hiroi hane wo motsu chiisana orenji iro no konchuu da. Totemo utsukushii

Major: A person with the wings and head of a monarch butterfly.
Mejaa: Chou no atama to tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a monarch butterfly.
Mejaa: Chou no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny flying insect that can be seen at night by its glowing tail.
Mejaa: Yakousei no tobu konchuu. Shiri wo hikaraseru koto ga dekiru.

Major: A person with the wings and head of a firefly.
Mejaa: Hotaru no atama to tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a firefly.
Mejaa: Hotaru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A relatively large insect found in swamps and marshland.
Mejaa: Mizube ya shitchitai de mirareru ookii konchuu.

Major: A person with the wings and head of a dragonfly.
Mejaa: Tonbo no atama to tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a dragonfly.
Mejaa: Tonbo no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small woolly insect that lives in hive colonies.  It has an annoying sting which it rarely uses.
Mejaa: Mure de su wo tsukuru kebukai konchuu. Metta ni tsukawanaiga, dokubari wo motsu
Youmou no you na mita me
Maru hanabachi no mitsurou no katamari
Joukika shita maru hanabachi no mitsurou
Joukika shita maru hanabachi no hachimitsu
Joukika shita maru hanabachi no hachimitsushu
Joukika shita maru hanabachi no dokueki

Major: A medium-Sized herbivore that lives in the high mountains, able to navigate the slopes despite its hooved feet.
Mejaa: Kouzan ni seisoku suru chuugata no soushoku doubutsu de, hizume no aru ashi ni mo kakawarazu gake wo idou suru koto ga dekimasu.

Major: A horned person with the head of a mountain goat.
Mejaa: Shiroiwayagi no atama to kado wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a mountain goat.
Mejaa: Shiroiwayagi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A person with the head and fur of a hoary marmot.
Mejaa: Maamotto no atama to kegawa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large creature the shape of a hoary marmot.
Mejaa: Maamotto no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge aquatic mammal with giant tusks and dense whiskers.  They are thick and blubbery and live almost exclusively on mussels.
Mejaa: Ookina kiba to hige ga tokuchou no oogata suisei honyuurui. Kairui ga shushoku.

Major: A giant monster in the form of a walrus.
Mejaa: Seiuchi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small oceanic eel-Like creature that latches onto the side of its victim and tears into them.
Mejaa: Shitai ni suitsuite taberu, chiisana unagi no you na seibutsu da.

Major: A giant oceanic fish with rows and rows of razor-Sharp pointed teeth.
Mejaa: Kamisori no you ni surudoi ha wo motsu, kyodai na kaiyougyo da.

Major: Ability to make one afraid to go into the water
Mejaa: Mizu ni hairu no wo osoresaseru

Major: A large eel-Like fish found in coastal waters.
Mejaa: Engan ni sumu ookina unagi no you na sakana.

Major: A large fish found in coastal temperate waters.
Mejaa: Ondan na engan kaiiki de mirareru ookina sakana.

Major: A huge fish covered with growths and spots it uses to hide on the sea bed.  It is not usually aggressive.
Mejaa: Kaitei ni sumu, hanten no aru kyodaigyo. Odayaka na seikaku.

Major: A gigantic filter-Feeding fish found in tropical oceans.
Mejaa: Nettai no umi ni seisoku suru, totemo kyodai na roka sesshokugyo.

Major: A large nocturnal bottom-Dwelling fish.  It is sluggish in movement and found in near-Tropical shores.
Mejaa: Yakousei no oogata teiseigyo. Ugoki ga osoku, nettai no engan ni seisoku.

Major: A large, aggressive, oceanic fish with a mouth full of pointed teeth.  It is capable of great speed.
Mejaa: Togatta ha wo takusan motsu, doumou na kaiyougyo. Totemo hayaku oyogu.

Major: A large fish which scavenges along tropical and temperate coastal waters.
Mejaa: Nettai oyobi ontai no engan suiiki ni seisoku suru, funiku shoku no kyodaigyo

Major: A giant, striped, oceanic fish known to devour anything in its path.
Mejaa: Shima moyou no aru kyodai kaiyougyo. Totemo neimou de, arayuru mono wo kui tsukusu.

Major: A medium-Sized, aggressive, territorial fish.  It can be found in shallow oceanic waters, and has also been known to travel up large rivers.
Mejaa: Neimou na chuugata gyorui. Asai kaiiki ni sumi, kawa wo sojou suru koto mo aru.

Major: A medium-Sized fish found in shallow oceanic waters.
Mejaa: Asase ni seisoku suru chuugata no same.

Major: A medium-Sized fish which shelters in caves on the shallow sea floor.  It hunts for food in packs but is not aggressive.
Mejaa: Asai kaitei no doukutsu ni hisomu chuugata no sakana. Mureta sakana wo taberuga, doumou de wa nai.

Major: A large, dangerous fish found hunting in packs in any ocean.
Mejaa: Zensekai no umi ni seisoku suru, mure wo tsukuru doumou de ookina nikushokugyo da.

Major: A large, flat, camouflaged fish found on the sea floor in temperate waters.  It is quite passive.
Mejaa: Ontai no kaitei ni seisoku suru, ookikute hirabettaku, gitai shite iru same da. Jitto shite ugokanai.
Kaitei ni seisoku suru chuugata no sakana.

Major: A huge filter-Feeding fish with great wings.  They travel the oceans and are curious and friendly.
Mejaa: Ookina hane wo motsu kyodai na roka sesshokugyo. Karera wa umi wo tabi shi, koukishin ousei de yuukouteki desu.

Major: A medium-Sized, flat fish.  It lives near the beach and will defend itself with sharp barbs.
Mejaa: A medium-Sized, flat fish.  It lives near the beach and will defend its erufu with sharp barbs.
A ka ei no chigyo no

Major: An elusive medium-Sized fish found in coastal waters.
Mejaa: Engan kaiiki de mirareru toraedokoro no nai chuugata no sakana.

Major: A large oceanic fish covered with bony plates.
Mejaa: Uroko kou de oowareta ookina umi no sakana.

Major: A medium-Sized fish found around coasts and islands.  It is easy prey for predators.
Mejaa: Kaigan ya shimajima de mirareru chuugata no sakana. Hoshokusha no ejiki ni nariyasui.

Major: A medium-Sized oceanic fish, often hunted for its meat.
A large oceanic fish.  It is flat, round and red.
Mejaa: Hirabettakute maruppoi, akairo no oogatakai suigyo.

Major: A large, big-Mouthed fish, found around coral reefs.
Mejaa: Sango shou ni seisoku suru, kuchi no ookina oogatagyo.

Major: A medium-Sized oceanic fish.  It is fork-Tailed and sought after for its meat.
Mejaa: Chuugata no kaisuigyo. Yoku shokuyou to shite ryou no emono ni sareru.

Major: A giant oceanic creature resembling a huge fish'S head connected to a wide tail.
Mejaa: Tai zentai ga marude ookina sakana no atama no you na katachi wo shita, oogatakai suigyo da.

Major: A huge predatory fish found in open ocean.  It has a long pointed bill which it uses to slash and ram.
Mejaa: Ookina gaiyou kaisuigyo. Ookina kado wo mochi, sore de tsukisashi tari kit tari suru.

Major: A huge oceanic fish capable of great speed.  It has a long, sharp snout used for slashing its prey.
Mejaa: Supiido ga hayai kyodai na umi no sakana. Emono wo kiru no ni tsukawareru nagakute surudoi hana ga arimasu.

Major: A large, flat, oceanic fish.  It dwells on the sea floor, both its eyes on the top side.
Mejaa: Ookikute taira na umi no sakana. Kaitei ni haritsuita mama ue ga mieru you, ryoume ga onaji men ni katayotte tsuite iru.

Major: A large, long fish with many sharp fangs.  It hunts by ambushing its prey.
Mejaa: Surudoi kiba ga takusan aru ookikute nagai sakana. Emono wo machibuse shite kari wo shimasu.

Major: A large oceanic fish capable of great speed.
Mejaa: Supiido ga hayai oogata no kaiyougyo.

Major: A medium-Sized sea mammal with a long thin horn on its nose.  It uses this horn to communicate and break up ice.
Mejaa: Hana ni nagaku hosoi kado wo motsu chuugata kaisei honyuurui. Kono kado wo tsukatte tsuushin shi, koori wo kudakimasu.

Major: A medium-Sized creature with the arms and torso on a man, but with the head and tail of a narwhal.
Mejaa: Ikkaku no atama to o wo motta ningen da. Ude wa tsuite iru.

Major: A huge sea monster with an enormous horn on its nose.
Mejaa: Hana ni kyodai na kado ga aru, baka dekai umi no kaibutsu da

Major: A huge, round, hairless river creature.  It is a plant-Eating animal but has long tusks and can be aggressive and deadly if disturbed.
Mejaa: Marukkokute ke ga haete inai, kawabe ni sumu oogata honyuurui da. Soushoku daga kiba ga nagaku, jama suru mono ni wa sono kiba de osoikakaru.

Major: A large person with the head of a hippo.
Mejaa: Kaba no atama wo motta ningen da.
Kaba no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized fish with a long snout.  It is found in lakes and streams.
Mejaa: Mizuumi ya ogawa ni sumu, hana no nagai chuugatagyo.

Major: A medium-Sized fish found in lakes and streams.  They are bottom-Feeders and tend to gather in groups.
Mejaa: Chuugata no tansuigyo. Suitei ni hisomi, murete iru koto ga ooi.

Major: A medium-Sized predatory fish found in lakes and streams.  It is known for its ferocious attacks and interlocking teeth.
Mejaa: Chuugata tansuigyo. Neimou na seikaku de, surudoi ha de kamitsuku.

Major: A medium-Sized, green fish found in temperate lakes.
Mejaa: Ontai no mizuumi ni sumu, midoriiro no chuugatagyo.

Major: A small semi-Aquatic, egg laying mammal with a bill, flat tail and poison spurs.
Mejaa: Kuchibashi, taira na o, doku no kezume wo motsu chiisana han suisei no sanran honyuurui.
Kyodai kamonohashi no kodomo no kodomo no

Major: A huge monster, the shape of a platypus.
Mejaa: Kamonohashi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge brown creature found in temperate woodland.  It is known for its ferocious attack, usually when it or its young are threatened.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni sumu, oogata honyuurui. Kigai wo kuwaeruto mouretsu na hangeki wo shite kuru.

Major: A large person with the head of a grizzly bear.
Mejaa: Higuma no atama wo motta ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a grizzly bear.
Mejaa: Higuma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large omnivorous predator found in temperate woodlands.  Mainly living on berries, it will also steal carcasses from other hunters.  Though normally a docile animal, it has been known to kill in a predatory attack.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni sumu oogata zasshoku honyuurui. Omoni kajitsu wo taberuga, hoka no nikushokujuu no emono wo yokodori mo suru. Fudan wa onkou daga, jiji doubutsu wo kari korosu.

Major: A large person with the head of a black bear.
Mejaa: Tsukinowa guma no atama wo motta ningen da.
Kyodai tsukinowa guma no kodomo no

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a black bear.
Mejaa: Tsukinowa guma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized hoofed forest creature that grows its antlers back each year.
Mejaa: Chuugata no soushoku doubutsu. Maitoshi edazuno ga haekawaru.

Major: A person with the head of a deer.
Mejaa: Shika no atama wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a deer.
Mejaa: Shika no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small carnivorous animal found in temperate climates.  It has orange fur and is known for its cleverness.
Mejaa: Ondan na kikou ni seisoku suru kogata nikushokujuu. Orenji iro no kegawa wo mochi, totemo kashikoi.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a fox.
Mejaa: Kitsune no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a fox.
Mejaa: Kitsune no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small omnivorous animal with a bright mask of fur.  It is nocturnal and found in temperate forests.  It is a curious animal and has been known to steal from civilized areas.
Mejaa: Kogata zasshoku honyuurui. Ontai no mori ni sumu. Koukishin ousei de, shibashiba hitozato kara nusumi wo okonau.

Major: A person with the mask and tail of a raccoon.
Mejaa: Araiguma no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a raccoon.
Mejaa: Araiguma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized monkey found in woods and grassland.  It usually lives on roots and insects but can become a pest in civilized areas, roaming in large groups and begging for scraps.
Mejaa: Mori ya sougen ni seisoku suru chuugata no saru. Futsuu wa ki no ne ya konchuu wo tabemasuga, hitozato de wa mure de gomi wo sunadotte tabe, gaijuu ni naru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a rhesus macaque.
Mejaa: Akage zaru no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the form of a rhesus macaque.
Mejaa: Akage zaru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large solitary feline.  It is found most often in dense vegetation, ambushing its prey.
Mejaa: Mitsurin ni seisoku suru oogata no nekoka doubutsu. Emono wo machibuse shite karu.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a cougar.
Mejaa: Pyuuma no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a cougar.
Mejaa: Pyuuma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large canine found in temperate regions.  It is territorial and hunts in packs.
Mejaa: Ontai ni seisoku suru oogata no inu. Nawabari wo mochi, mure de kari wo suru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a wolf.
Mejaa: Ookami no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a wolf.
Mejaa: Ookami no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large, round, lowland rodent.  It lives in burrows in the ground and ventures out to eat.
Mejaa: Marukkoi oogatage pparui. Teichi ni seisoku suru. Jimen ni suana wo horu.

Major: A person with the head and fur of a groundhog.
Mejaa: Uddo chakku no atama to kegawa wo motsu ningen da.
Kyodai uddo chakku no kodomo no

Major: A large creature the shape of a groundhog.
Mejaa: Uddo chakku no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge reptile, found in rivers and marshlands.  It is an ambush predator, solitary and territorial.
Mejaa: Numa ya shitchi ni seisoku suru oogata hachuurui. Mure wo tsukurazu, machibusete kari wo suru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of an alligator.
Mejaa: Arigeetaa no atama wo o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of an alligator.
Mejaa: Arigeetaa no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized, red-Faced black bird that searches the temperate lands for carrion.
Mejaa: Kuroiro no karada ni akai kao wo shita, chuugata no funiku shoku no tori da.

Major: A person with the head and wings of a buzzard.
Mejaa: Nosuri no atama wo tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a buzzard.
Mejaa: Nosuri no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large bear-Like creature with a striking coat of black and white hair.  It feeds on bamboo forests.
Mejaa: Shirokuro no kimyou na kegawa wo motta ookina kuma da. Take wo taberu.
Ookina fuwafuwa no atama to hara

Major: A giant bear-Like creature found in the wildest parts of the world.  It has striking black and white fur.
Mejaa: Shiro to kuro no kegawa wo motsu oogata no kuma da.

Major: A humanoid creature with the head and belly of a panda.
Mejaa: Panda no atama wo hara wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A medium-Sized semi-Aquatic rodent.  It lives in large herds and barks when alarmed.
Mejaa: Chuugata no han suisei gesshi doubutsu. Ookina mure wo tsukuri, odorokuto ookina koe de naku.

Major: A huge rodent that walks on tall legs.  Its bark can be heard at large distances.  It is fond of swimming.
Mejaa: Oogata no geh harui. Sono nakigoe wa tooku kara de mo kikoeru. Oyogi ga umai.

Major: A humanoid with the head of a capybara.  It is fond of swimming.
Mejaa: Kabi para no atama wo motsu ningen da. Oyogi ga umai.

Major: A small mammal with a striped face.  It lives in groups and is ferocious in combat.
Mejaa: Shima moyou no kao wo motta kogata honyuurui. Mure wo tsukuri, igai to neimou da.

Major: A humanoid with the head and stripes of a badger.
Mejaa: Anaguma no atama wo motsu shima moyou no ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a badger.  It is ferocious in combat.
Mejaa: Anaguma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da. Neimou ni tatakau.

Major: A large mammal with great antlers and a large nose. It lives in temperate forests.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni sumu, ookina edazuno to ookina hana wo motsu shika no nakama da.

Major: A humanoid with the head and antlers of a moose.
Mejaa: Herajika no atama to kado wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a moose.
Mejaa: Herajika no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small tree-Dwelling mammal with distinctive color.  It rears up on its hind legs when cornered.  It uses its front paws like hands.
Mejaa: Dokutoku no iro wo shita chiisana ki ni seisoku suru honyuurui. Oitsumerareru to ushiroashi de tachiagaru. Maeashi wo te no you ni tsukai konasu.

Major: A medium-Sized, walking red panda with arms and a tail.  It prefers the forest and its beloved trees.
Mejaa: Te to o wo motta chuugata no ressaa panda.
Kyodai ressaa panda no kodomo no

Major: A large monster with the shape of a red panda.
Mejaa: Ressaa panda no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge, hairless mammal, found grazing in grasslands in groups.  It eats plants which it lifts up with its long trunk.  When angered, it will attack with its long tusks.
Mejaa: Sabanna ni seisoku suru oogata soushoku honyuurui. Nagai hana wo tsukatte shokubutsu wo taberu. Mure wo tsukuri, osowareta toki wa nagai kiba wo tsukatte hangeki suru.

Major: A large person with the trunk and ears of an elephant.
Mejaa: Zou no doutai to mimi wo motta, kyodai na ningen da.

Major: A gigantic monster in elephant form.
Mejaa: Zou no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized animal living in grass and woodland.  It has a large snout with four sharp tusks.  It will aggressively defend itself.
Mejaa: Kusa ya mori ni seisoku suru chuugata no doubutsu. 4tsu no surudoi kiba wo motsu ookina hana wo motsu. Sekkyokuteki ni mi wo mamoru.

Major: A person with the head of a warthog.
Mejaa: Ibo inoshishi no atama wo motsu ningen da.
Kyodai ibo inoshishi no ko no

Major: A huge monster warthog with jagged tusks.
Mejaa: Ibo inoshishi no sugata de Giza kiza no kiba wo motsu, kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large ferocious predator found in grasslands.  It lives in groups of females and one male with a large mane.  They hunt together and are capable of felling extremely large prey.
Mejaa: Sabanna ni seisoku suru oogata nikushoku honyuurui. Osu wa ookina tategami wo mochi, fukusuu no mesu to haaremu wo tsukuru. Kari no sai wa Haaremu de kyouryoku shite mizukara yori ookina emono wo karu.

Major: A person with the head of a lion.
Mejaa: Raion no atama wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A gigantic version of the feline predator.  Its giant prides can be found in the wildest, most savage parts of the world.
Mejaa: Kyodai na hyakujuu no ou da. Mottomo hokori takaku, kiken na chiiki ni seisoku suru.

Major: A large spotted feline found in grass and woodland.  It is known for great speed in hunting.
Mejaa: Mori ya sougen ni seisoku suru oogata nekoka doubutsu. Subayai kari wo suru.

Major: A large, muscular, spotted feline found in tropical jungles.  It is solitary and stalks and ambushes its prey.
Mejaa: Janguru ni seisoku suru kinnikushitsu no hanten no aru oogata nekoka doubutsu. Kodoku de, emono wo tsukamae, machibuse suru.

Major: A gigantic feline predator, similar to its cousins in all but size.  It can be found in the savage wilderness.
Mejaa: Ookisa igai wa jagaa ni sokkuri na kyodai na kaibutsu da. Yaban na arano ni seisoku suru.

Major: A huge, striped predator.  It is found in almost any climate on a lone hunt for its prey.
Mejaa: Shima no oogata hoshokusha da. Arayuru kikou de mirare, mure wo tsukurazu, kari wo suru.

Major: An orange striped person with the head of a tiger.
Mejaa: Tora no you na atama wo motsu, kuro ki no shima moyou no karada no ningen da.

Major: The largest of the giant cats.  It can be found hunting alone in the most savage countryside.
A large spotted feline predator.  It is capable of incredible speed when ambushing its prey.
Mejaa: Oogata no nekoka doubutsu. Emono wo machibuse shi, tondemo nai sokudo de oikakete kuru.

Major: A spotted person with the head and tail of a cheetah.
Mejaa: Chiitaa no atama to karada wo motsu, hanten no aru karada wo shita ningen da.

Major: A gigantic spotted cat.  It is possibly the fastest animal on land and is found in the savage wilds.
Mejaa: Baka dekai chiitaa da. Rikujou seibutsu de mottomo ashi ga hayai.

Major: A small hooved creature found in large groups in the grasslands.  It has short horns and moves by leaps and bounds.
Mejaa: Sougen ni seisoku suru, ookina mure wo tsukuru kogata no soushoku doubutsu da. Chiisana kado wo mochi, chokomaka ugokimawaru.

Major: A horned person with the head of a gazelle.
Mejaa: Gazeru no atama to kado wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a gazelle.
Mejaa: Gazeru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large monkey with blue face and rump.  It lives in large groups and often survives by destroying crops and stealing garbage.  The males are larger, with powerful jaws.
Mejaa: Aoi kao to shikori wo motsu oogata no saru. Ookina mure wo tsukuri, hatake wo arashi tari zanpan wo sunadot tari suru meiwakusha. Osu wa chikarazuyoi ago wo motsu.

Major: A blue-Rumped person with the head and tail of a mandrill.
Mejaa: Mandoriru no atama to o wo motsu, massao na kao wo shita ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the form of a mandrill.
Mejaa: Mandoriru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na ningen da.

Major: A large ape which lives in the tropical forests.  It lives in complex social groups of many members.  Though it is quite intelligent, it has been known for ferocious attacks.
Mejaa: Nettairin ni seisoku suru oogatarui jin'en. Ooku no menbaa kara naru fukuzatsu na shakai shuudan ni seisoku shite imasu. Hijou ni chiteki na mono desuga, mouretsu na kougeki de shirarete imasu.

Major: A large ape which lives in the tropical forests.  It is quite intelligent and lives in large and complex social groups.
Mejaa: Janguru ni seisoku suru oogata no saru da. Totemo kashikoku, fukuzatsu de kyodai na shakaiteki guruupu wo tsukuru.

Major: A huge ape found in the forest.  It lives in small groups eating plants.  The groups are lead by a large dominant male with a silver back.
Mejaa: Mori ni seisoku suru oogatarui jin'en. Shokubutsu shoku de, chiisana mure wo tsukuru. Shirubaa pakku to yobareru riidaa ga mure wo shihai shite iru.

Major: A medium-Sized ape found in the trees.  It is known for its loud calls.
Mejaa: Jujousei no chuugatarui jin'en. Oogoe de sakebu.

Major: Ability to swing through the trees
A small fruit-Eating ape, found in the trees.
Mejaa: Jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Kajitsu ga shushoku.

Major: A small ape found in the trees of the tropical forest.  It is known for its calls.
Mejaa: Janguru ni seisoku suru, jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Kawatta hoegoe de naku.

Major: A small ape found in the trees eating fruit.
Mejaa: Jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Kajitsu ga shushoku.

Major: A small ape found in pairs, swinging from the trees.
Mejaa: Jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Fuufu de kurasu.
Shiroi boushi no you na moyou

Major: A small ape that swings from the trees, eating fruit.
Mejaa: Jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Kajitsu ga shushoku.
Ami no you na karafuru na moyou

Major: A small ape from the tropical forest.  It can be found in the trees eating fruit.
Mejaa: Jujousei no kogatarui jin'en. Kajitsu ga shushoku.

Major: A large long-Necked creature with a large hump on its sturdy body.  It has been domesticated to carry passengers and cargo but is nonetheless bad-Tempered and will spit.
Mejaa: Ookina kobu to nagai kubi wo motsu oogata honyuurui. Kachiku to shite hito ya nimotsu wo hakoberuga, kishou ga araku, shibashiba tsuba wo haki kakete kuru.

Major: A person with the head and hump of a one-Humped camel.
Mejaa: Hitokoburakuda no atama to kobu wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a one-Humped camel.
Mejaa: Hitokoburakuda no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large, long-Necked creature with two fleshy humps on its back.  It is domesticated to carry passengers and cargo.
Mejaa: Futatsu no kobu to nagai kubi wo motta oogata honyuurui. Kachiku to shite hito ya nimotsu wo hakoberu.

Major: A person with the head and humps of a two-Humped camel.
Mejaa: Futakoburakuda no atama to kobu wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a two-Humped camel.
Mejaa: Futakoburakuda no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge, predatory reptile found in coastal marshes and river deltas.  It ambushes its prey at the shore and uses its great size to drag the victim under and drown them.
Mejaa: Engan no shitchi ya sankaku shuu ni seisoku suru oogata nikushoku hachuurui. Kishi de emono wo machibuse shi, kyotai wo ikashite karada no shita ni hikizurikomi, dekishi saseru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a saltwater crocodile.
Mejaa: Irie wani no atama to o wo motta ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a saltwater crocodile.
Mejaa: Irie wani no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large bird with a featherless red head found in the sky of tropical deserts, scanning the ground for dead carcasses.
Mejaa: Nettai no sabaku ni seisoku suru oogata no tori. Ke no nai akairo no atama wo mochi, funiku wo sunadoru.

Major: A person with the head and wings of a vulture.
Mejaa: Hagetaka no atama wo tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a vulture.
Mejaa: Hagetaka no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge herbivore with thick plated skin and powerful build.  It is known for the thick horns on the end of its nose.
Mejaa: Buatsui kawa wo motsu oogata soushoku honyuurui. Hana no ue ni futoi kado ga aru.

Major: A person with the head and horns of a rhinoceros.
Mejaa: Sai no atama to kado wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a rhinoceros.
Mejaa: Sai no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge leaf-Eating mammal.  It has an extremely long neck.  Its skin has a distinctive brown and white pattern.
Mejaa: Nagai kubi no oogata soushoku honyuurui. Shiro to kasshoku no tokuchouteki na haishoku no moyou no karada wo shite iru.

Major: A person with the head and neck of a giraffe.
Mejaa: Kirin no atama to kubi wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster the shape of a giraffe.
Mejaa: Kirin no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small mammal known to defend itself ferociously in combat, often fighting off multiple animals many times its size.
Mejaa: Hijou ni neimou na kogata honyuurui. Jibun no nan bai mo no ookisa no teki to tatakau.

Major: A humanoid with the head and stripes of a honey badger.
Mejaa: Raa teru no atama wo motsu shima moyou no ningen da.
Kyodai Raa teru no kodomo no

Major: A huge monster the shape of a honey badger.  It is ferocious in combat.
Mejaa: Raa teru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da. Hijou ni neimou.

Major: A medium-Sized reptile with a large shell.  It can retreat into its shell to escape predators.
Mejaa: Ookina koura wo motsu, chuugata ryouseirui. Osowareta toki wa teashi wo koura no naka ni hikkomete mi wo mamoru.

Major: A huge monster with an enormous shell.
Mejaa: Baka dekai koura wo motsu kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small mammal with a leathery hide.  It can roll into a ball to escape predators.
Mejaa: Katai kawa wo motta kogata doubutsu. Booru no you ni marumatte teki kara mi wo mamoru.
Uroko no you na yoroi no hada

Major: A person with the hide and head of an armadillo.
Mejaa: Arumajiro no atama to hifu wo motta ningen da.

Major: A large monster the shape of an armadillo.  It has thick armor for skin.
Mejaa: Arumajiro no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da. Yoroi no you na hada wo motsu.

Major: A large hooved animal with curved horns and a thick brown coat.  It is known for its strong odor.
Mejaa: Magatta kado to atsui chairo no kegawa wo motsu oogata honyuurui. Nioi ga tsuyoi.

Major: A horned person with the head of a muskox.
Mejaa: Jakou ushi no atama to kado wo motsu ningen da.
Kyodai jakou ushi no ko no

Major: A huge monster in the form of a muskox.
Mejaa: Jakou ushi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large hooved animal found roaming wild in temperate forests.  The males have long antlers.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni seisoku suru, oogata honyuurui. Osu wa ookina edazuno wo motsu.

Major: A person with the head of an elk.
Mejaa: Kijirijika no atama wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of an elk.
Mejaa: Kijirijika no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge predatory mammal covered in white hair.  It hunts the shores along tundra and glaciers.
Mejaa: Shiroi ke de oowareta oogata nikushoku honyuurui. Kyokkan no umibe de kari wo suru.

Major: A large person with the head of a polar bear.
Mejaa: Shirokuma no atama wo motta ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a polar bear.
Mejaa: Shirokuma no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small, muscular, weasel-Like creature.  It is known for its ferocity.
Mejaa: Chiisakute kinnikushitsu no, itachi no you na ikimono. Hijou ni kyoubou.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a wolverine.
Mejaa: Kuzuri no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large, terrifying monster the shape of a wolverine.
Mejaa: Kuzuri no you na sugata wo shita osoroshii kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny furry rodent dwelling in the hollow cracks of rocks.  They can be found high in the mountains.
Mejaa: Iwa no kubonda wareme ni sumu, fusafusa no kogata gesshi doubutsu. Takayama chitai ni seisoku.

Major: A hairy person with the head and tail of a chinchilla.
Mejaa: Chinchira no atama to o wo motsu, fusafusa no ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a chinchilla.
Mejaa: Chinchira no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large quadruped with a mane circling its manlike face and hands at the end of its forelimbs.  It lives underground and is fond of raiding the supplies of cavern outposts.
Mejaa: Ookina tategami wo motta, yotsunbai no enjin da. Chika ni sunde ite, doukutsu no zenshou kichi no busshi wo shuugeki suru.

Major: A small underground monster that crawls across the cavern wall with its four clawed hands.  It has a single large eye which can shine with its own light, otherwise its stony skin blends in with the rock.  It has no mouth and is said to feed on evil alone.
Mejaa: 4pon no kagizume de doukutsu no kabe wo hau chiisana chika no kaibutsu. Jishin de hikari wo hanatsu, ookina hitotsume wo motsu. Me wo tsubureba ishi no you na hada de iwa ni magireru. Sore wa kuchi ga naku, hitori de aku wo taberu to iwareru.

Major: A huge cave monster with hundreds of feet moving along the bottom of its long body.  In place of a head, it has an enormous toothy maw.
Mejaa: Suuhyaku fiito mo no nagai karada de doukutsu wo haimawaru kaibutsu da. Atama no kawari ni ha no haeta kyodai na ibukuro wo motsu.

Major: A large cavern-Dwelling humanoid monster.  It has a gaping mouth with many sharp teeth.  It has no eyes and only two digits on each hand and foot.
Mejaa: Doukutsu ni sumu ookina hitogata no kaibutsu. Kuchi ga ookiku, surudoi ha wo motsu. Me ga naku, sorezore no teashi ni nipon zutsu shika yubi ga nai.

Major: A tiny amphibian with a long prehensile tail.  It lives in underground swamps and tower-Cap forests on which it feeds.
Mejaa: Nagai shippo wo motsu kogata ryouseirui. Shippo de kabe ni tsukawaru koto ga deki, tawaa kyappu no mawari de esa wo tsukamaeru.

Major: A small rock-Eating creature that lives in molten rock.  It scurries on little feet and swims through liquid rock with sharp wings.  It uses magma to digest rock and spits out burning globs.
Mejaa: Maguma no naka ni sumu, iwa kui no kaibutsu. Chiisana ashi de haimawari, maguma wo surudoi hire de oyogimawaru. Iwa wo shouka shite, atsui tsuba wo tobashite kougeki suru.

Major: A tiny underground monster with large claws and horns.  It walks on two legs and is dangerous when encountered in large numbers.
Mejaa: Ookina tsume to kado wo motsu chiisana chika kaibutsu da. Ryouashi de aruku no de, takusan deauto kiken.

Major: A fearsome, long-Toothed mouth the size of a man'S head, flying on bat wings.  It is found in deep caves.
Mejaa: Hito no atama hodo no nagai ha wo motta ookina kuchi ni, koumori no hane ga haete iru. Doukutsu shinbu wo tobimawaru.

Major: A large ball of skin found moving around the debris near underground ponds.  It is there that it absorbs dead matter for food.
Mejaa: Haizurimawaru hada no aru ookina nikukai. Chiteiko no mawari no shigai wo taberu.

Major: A large creature found grazing on mushrooms deep underground.  It walks on two legs and has the head of a bird with the antlers of a great elk.
Mejaa: Chitei no kinoko no mawari ni seisoku suru oogata seibutsu. Shika no you na ookina edazuno wo mochi, nipon no ashi de arukimawaru.

Major: A snake-Like creature living deep underground.  Its head is covered in armor so that is resembles the head of a dragon.
Mejaa: Chika fukaku ni sumu hebi no you na ikimono. Sono atama wa yoroi de oowarete ori, doragon no atama ni nite iru
Joukika shita kabuto hebi no dokueki

Major: A medium-Sized monster walking on two clawed legs.  It has two mouths on the ends of a pair of tentacles.  It uses its mouths to digest its victims with acid and rows of razor-Like teeth.
Mejaa: 2pon no tsume de aruku chuugata no kaibutsu. 1 tai no shokushu no hashi ni 2tsu no kuchi ga ari, kuchi wo tsukatte giseisha wo san to kamisori no you na ha no retsu de shouka suru.

Major: A huge monster with an enormous tail, covered with thick fur.  They run on four legs and can be found deep under the earth.
Mejaa: Futoi kegawa de oowareta kyodai na o wo motsu, oogata no monsutaa. 4pon no ashi de hashiri, chitei fukaku ni sumu.

Major: A tiny underground creature made of a mass of appendages resembling human fingers.  It creeps across the ground like a starfish and eats with a mouth on the bottom of its body.
Mejaa: Ningen no yubi ni nita fuzokushi no katamari de dekita chiisana chika seibutsu. Hitode no you ni jimen wo haimawari, karada no soko ni kuchi wo motte taberu.

Major: A large, long-Bodied grazer with a thick mane that feeds on the tops of towercap mushrooms deep under the earth.
Mejaa: Chikyuu no okufukaku ni aru tawaa kyappu no kinoko no teppen wo taberu, tategami ga atsui, ookikute karada no nagai soushoku doubutsu.

Major: A gigantic version of its tiny cousin, this long, slimy creature tunnels through the rocks deep underground.
Mejaa: Chika no iwa wo horisusumu kyodai na mimizu da.

Major: A man-Shaped abomination made entirely of blood.  These cursed creatures are only found very near the underworld.
Mejaa: Kanzen ni chi de dekita ningen no katachi wo shita bakemono. Korera no norowareta ikimono wa, meikai no sugu chikaku de shika mitsukarimasen.

Major: A creature that crawls along the cavern ceiling with four long arms.  Its body is shaped as the head of a man with a mouth full of shark teeth.  It waits for its prey to pass below.
Mejaa: 4pon no nagai ude de doukutsu no tenjou ni sotte hau, ikimono. Sono karada wa same no ha de ippai no kuchi wo motsu otoko no atama no katachi wo shite iru. Emono ga shita wo tsuuka suru no wo machibuseru.

Major: A hideous monster that has the body of a giant mole-Rat and the torso of a mole-Rat man.   It is found deep underground.
Mejaa: Hadakadebanezumi no atama to karada wo motta ningen da. Chika fukaku ni seisoku suru.

Major: A huge monster that lurks in caverns deep under the earth.  It uses its wide beak to reach down and pluck up unsuspecting intruders.
Mejaa: Chika fukaku no doukutsu ni hisomu kyodai na monsutaa. Hiroi kuchibashi wo tsukatte, muboubi na shinnyuusha ni te wo nobashite hoshoku suru.

Major: A small creature that lives in watery ditches deep underground.  It has a sharp beak and four tentacles with claws at the end.
Mejaa: Chika fukaku no kawa ni sumu chiisana ikimono. Surudoi kuchibashi to 4pon no tsume no tsuita shokushu wo motsu.

Major: A huge emaciated-Looking bear with great drooping ears and many sharp teeth.  It is found deep underground.
Mejaa: Ookina taresagatta mimi to ooku no surudoi ha wo motsu kyodai na yaseotoroeta you ni mieru kuma. Chika fukaku ni seisoku suru.

Major: A gigantic monster, once a dragon, now adapted to and polluted by the underground.  Its wings fall limp at its side.  Its face is full of incredibly long teeth.  Its eyes are large to penetrate the darkness.
Mejaa: Chika ni tekiou shite daraku shita doragon da. Hane wa yowayowashiku yokotawari., Kao wa shinjirarenai hodo nagai kiba wo takusan motsu. Me wa ookikute kurayami wo mitoosu.

Major: A humanoid monster found lurking far underground.  It feigns death, usually near water, until a victim passes by.  It then uses its long arms to drag its prey into the water to drown or strangle them.
Mejaa: Chika fukaku ni seisoku suru hitogata seibutsu. Mizu no soba de gishi wo okonai, nagai ude wo tsukatte emono wo suichuu ni hikizurikomi, dekishi sase tari shimekoroshi tari suru.

Major: A small, round humanoid found wandering the caves deep underground.  Most of its body is taken up by a huge tusked mouth.
Mejaa: Karada no daibubun ga kiba no haeta ookina kuchi no, marukkokute chiisana hitogata seibutsu da.

Major: A floating pod with eye-Stalks.  It can spray poison and it gives off poison gas when punctured.
Mejaa: Me no gara ga aru sora tobu tsubo da. Doku wo fukikake, wareruto doku wo mawari ni makichirasu.

Major: A small humanoid resembling a walking mushroom with arms and legs.  It lives far underground near water and soil.
Mejaa: Ude to ashi no aru, kinoko ni nita hitogata seibutsu. Chika fukaku no mizube ni seisoku suru.
Toketa kabuto take otoko no soshiki
Joukika shita kabuto take otoko no soshiki

Major: A strange shapeless life form with an orange leathery skin containing a liquid interior.  It can secrete its internal fluid.
Mejaa: Orenji iro no kawabukuro no you na hifu wo motsu, kimyou na futeikei no seibutsu. Taieki ga juuman shite ori, sore wo bunpitsu suru.

Major: A strange crystalline creature the shape of a man.  It is found deep underground.
Mejaa: Murasaki suishou no karada wo motsu hitogata seibutsu. Chika fukaku ni seisoku suru.

Major: A medium-Sized underwater mollusk with eight arms.  It is the most clever of its kind.
Mejaa: 8pon no ude wo motsu chuugata no suichuu nantai doubutsu. Sore wa sono shu no naka de mottomo kashikoi.

Major: A dangerous water monster known for attacking ships at sea.
Mejaa: Fune wo osou kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny shelled ocean creature with many long legs.  It has two large pincers on its front limbs.
Mejaa: Nagai ashi ga takusan aru chiisana kaisei koukakurui. Zenshi ni 2tsu no ookina hasami ga aru.

Major: A person with the head and pincers of a crab.
Mejaa: Kani no atama to hasami wo motta ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a crab.
Mejaa: Kani no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A large predatory amphibious mammal.  It is difficult to evade once in the water.
Mejaa: Oogata no nikushoku honyuurui. Suichuu de osowaretara, nigeru koto wa muzukashii.

Major: A legless person with the head and back flippers of a leopard seal.
Mejaa: Hyou azarashi no atama to obire wo motsu, ashi no nai ningen da.
Kyodai hyou azarashi no kodomo no

Major: A giant monster in the form of a leopard seal.
Mejaa: Hyou azarashi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A person with a cuttlefish in place of a head.

Major: A huge sea monster in the shape of a cuttlefish.
Mejaa: Ika you na sugata wo shita kyodai na umi no kaibutsu da.

Major: A huge ocean mammal.  It is a vicious predator and can hunt in groups.
Mejaa: Oogata kaisei honyuurui. Osoroshii hoshokusha de, mure de kari wo suru.

Major: An aquatic person in the shape of an orca with arms.
Mejaa: Shachi no sugata ni ude no haeta suisei ningen da.

Major: A gigantic monster in the shape of an orca.
Mejaa: Shachi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny sea creature which dwells on the ocean floor, devoid of senses or motion.
Mejaa: Kaitei ni nezuita, ugokanai kankaku no nai chiisana ikimono.

Major: A person in the form of a sponge with arms and legs.
Mejaa: Kaimen ni teashi ga haeta sugata no ningen da.

Major: A tiny sea animal that lives in the sand just offshore.  It has a flat body with legs underneath.
Mejaa: Okiai no sunahama ni seisoku suru chiisana umi no doubutsu. Karada wa taira de, shita ni ashi ga aru

Major: A person with the head, shell, and tail of a horseshoe crab.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a horseshoe crab.
Mejaa: Kabutogani no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A giant marine mammal with a toothy jaw.
Mejaa: Tsuyoi ago wo motta oogata kaisei seibutsu.

Major: A huge person with the head and flippers of a sperm whale.

Major: A gigantic monster in the shape of a sperm whale.
Mejaa: Makkou kujira you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A person with the head and flippers of an elephant seal.
Mejaa: Zouazarashi no atama to obire wo motta ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of an elephant seal.
Mejaa: Zouazarashi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small marine mammal.  Its young are prized for their white fur.
Mejaa: Chiisana kairiku honyuurui da. Shiro no kegawa ni takai kachi ga aru.

Major: A person with the head and flippers of a harp seal.
Mejaa: Tategoto azarashi no atama to obire wo motta ningen da.
Kyodai tategoto azarashi no kodomo no

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a harp seal.
Mejaa: Tategoto azarashi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny, mollusk with a large shell and many tentacles.
Mejaa: Ookina kara to tasuu no shokushu wo motta kogata kaisei nantai seibutsu.

Major: A person with the shell and tentacles of a nautilus.
Mejaa: Oumu gai no kara to shokushu wo motta ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a nautilus.
Mejaa: Oumu gai no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small mammal noted for its tenacity.  It has long ears and flashing eyes.
Mejaa: Sono nebarizuyosa de yuumei na chiisana honyuurui. Mimi ga nagaku,me ga tenmetsu shimasu.
Deichuu ni seisoku suru, kogata ryouseirui.

Major: An insidious form of vermin.  It lives only to steal food from others.
Mejaa: Tabemono wo kuiarasu, jaaku na sugata no gaijuu da.

Major: Diabolical hunger for the food of others
Mejaa: Tanin no shokumotsu ni taisuru akumateki na kiga

Major: A fluffy, pudge-Filled being, known for its warm heart and stumble bumblings.
Mejaa: Fuwafuwa shitete marumaru to futori, atatakakute yochiyochi aruku.

Major: A tiny reptile, running on two legs.  It has a horn on the end of its nose.
Mejaa: 2pon no ashi de hashiru chiisana hachuurui. Hana no saki ni kado ga aru.

Major: A tiny creature made up of a series of crackling knobs set at strange angles.
Mejaa: Kimyou na kakudo ni settei sareta ichiren no pachipachi to iu nobu de kousei sareta chiisana ikimono.

Major: A tiny translucent creature, found in evil forests.
Mejaa: Han toumei no kogata no kumo. Jaaku na mori ni seisoku suru.
Joukika shita fantomu supaidaa no dokueki

Major: An insect many times the size of its peers.  It is known for its deafening buzz.
Mejaa: Hoka no hae yori nan bai mo ookii. Mimi wo tsunzaku you na haoto wo tateru.

Major: A tiny insect with a pulsating, lumpy body.  It is an evil bug that seeks blood.
Mejaa: Gotsugotsu shita chiisana konchuu. Sono karada wa myakudou shi, chi wo motomete tobimawaru jaaku na mushi da.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a lizard.
Mejaa: Tokage no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of a lizard.
Mejaa: Tokage no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A relatively large lizard.  It can be found in most climates, foraging for bugs during daylight hours.
Mejaa: Hikakuteki ookina tokage. Hotondo no kikou de mirare, nitchuu wa mushi wo sagashimasu.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a skink.
Mejaa: Ootokage no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A colorful lizard that spends its life hunting insects with its long tongue.  It moves slowly through the trees, spying the surroundings with its independently roving eyes.
Mejaa: Nagai shita de konchuu wo karu tokage. Kigi no aida wo yukkuri to idou shi, dokuritsu shita ugoki no aru me de mimawasu. Kakureru tame ni taishoku wo kaeru koto ga dekiru.

Major: A colorful person with the head and tail of a chameleon.
Mejaa: Kamereon no atama to o wo motsu karafuru na ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a chameleon.
Mejaa: Kamereon no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small lizard with adhesive feet for climbing.  It can change color from brown to green to fit its surroundings.
Mejaa: Touhanyou no nenchakusei no ashi ga tsuita chiisana tokage. Shuui ni awasete chairo kara midoriiro ni kaeru koto ga dekimasu.

Major: A person with the head and tail of an anole.
Mejaa: Anooru tokage no atama wo o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of an anole.
Mejaa: Anooru tokage no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A relatively large arboreal lizard found in the tropical forests.  Though it is a vegetarian, and mainly docile, it may whip with its extremely long tail when angered.
Mejaa: Nettairin de mirareru hikakuteki ookina jujousei no tokage. Soushokusei de onkou daga, okoruto hijou ni nagai o de muchi wo uchisueru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of an iguana.
Mejaa: Iguana no atama wo o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the shape of an iguana.
Mejaa: Iguana no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small river mammal with a long body.  They enjoy eating shellfish and other small animals.
Mejaa: Kawa ni sumu nagai dou no kogata honyuurui da. Kai ya kozakana wo konomu.

Major: A small marine mammal with a long body.  They enjoy eating shellfish and other small animals.
Mejaa: Umi ni sumu nagai dou no kogata honyuurui da. Kai ya kozakana wo konomu.

Major: A person with the long body and head of an otter.
Mejaa: Rakko no atama to nagai dou wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the form of an otter.
Mejaa: Rakko no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A medium-Sized reptile with a thick shell, which it can retreat into when threatened.  This creature can administer a painful bite.
Mejaa: Atsui koura wo motsu chuugata no hachuurui de, koura ni hikkomu koto ga dekiru. Kono ikimono wa itami wo tomonau koushou wo ataeru.

Major: A large reptile with a thick ridged shell.  It has been known to consume snakes and smaller turtles, and its bite can amputate fingers.
Mejaa: Atsui koura wo motsu ookina hachuurui. Hebi ya chiisana kame wo esa to shi, kamitsukareru to yubi wo setsudan shikane nai.

Major: A person with the shell and head of a snapping turtle.
Mejaa: Wani game no atama to koura wo motta ningen da.

Major: A large monster with an enormous shell and immensely powerful jaw.
Mejaa: Baka dekai koura to kyouryoku na ago wo motsu kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small river mammal with a flat tail, known for building wooden dams.
Mejaa: Kawa ni sumu chiisana honyuurui. Ki de damu wo tsukuru.

Major: A person with the head and flat tail of a beaver.
Mejaa: Biibaa no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large river monster, known for building huge wooden fortresses.
Mejaa: Kyodai na ki no yousai wo tateru, kyodai na kawa no kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny, aquatic, worm-Like creature that feeds on blood.
Mejaa: Suisei no imomushi no you na kyuuketsu seibutsu da.

Major: A large slug-Like creature with the torso of a man.  Its face is a mockery of teeth and slime.
Mejaa: Ningen no karada wo motsu namekuji no you na ikimono da. Kao ni nebaneba shita mono de dekita, nise no ha ga aru.

Major: A large monster in the shape of a leech.
Mejaa: Hiru no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small salamander found in remote lakes.  It has the mysterious ability to regrow limbs.
Mejaa: Ike ni sumu chiisana sanshou uo. Teashi ga saisei dekiru.

Major: A person with the head and tail of an axolotl.
Mejaa: Uupaaruupaa no atama wo o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster in the shape of an axolotl.
Mejaa: Uupaaruupaa no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small, predatory, weasel-Like mammal.  It is also semi-Aquatic.
Mejaa: Itachi no you na kogata no hoshokusha. Han suisei.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a mink.
Mejaa: Minku no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster in the form of a mink.
Mejaa: Minku no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny reptile with a shell on its back.  It can be found in rivers and ponds.
Mejaa: Kawa ya ike ni sumu, senaka ni koura wo motsu kogata hachuurui.

Major: A person with the head and shell of a pond turtle.
Mejaa: Buchi ishigame no atama to koura wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge monster shaped like a pond turtle.
Mejaa: Buchi ishigame no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny rodent that burrows by day and scurries about at night.
Mejaa: Hiruma wa ana wo hori,ya wa hashirimawaru chiisana gesshi doubutsu.

Major: A person with the head and fur of a hamster.
Mejaa: Hamusutaa no atama to kegawa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large creature the shape of a hamster.
Mejaa: Hamusutaa no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small round mammal whose back is covered in spines.  It is nocturnal and feeds on insects.  It curls into a ball when startled and is found in temperate regions.
Mejaa: Senaka ga toge de oowarete iru chiisana marui honyuurui. Yakousei de konchuu shoku. Odoroita toki ni marumatte mi wo mamoru. Ontai chiiki de mitsukarimasu.

Major: A person with the head and spines of a hedgehog.
Mejaa: Harinezumi no atama to hari wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster with the shape of a hedgehog.
Mejaa: Harinezumi no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny grey rodent that is only active at night.  It can sail between trees on wings stretching between its front and hind legs.
Mejaa: Yakousei de haiiro no kogata gesshi doubutsu. Maeashi to ushiroashi no aida ni nobiru tsubasa wo tsukatte kigi no aida wo tobimawaru.

Major: A person with the head and wings of a flying squirrel.
Mejaa: Momonga no atama wo tsubasa wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A large monster taking the shape of a flying squirrel.
Mejaa: Momonga no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small, intelligent vermin with a long naked tail.
Mejaa: Nagai shippo wo motta kashikoi gaijuu da.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a rat.
Mejaa: Nezumi no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A small grey rodent found chirping in the trees of temperate woodlands.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni sumu, haiiro no chiisana geh harui da.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a gray squirrel.
Mejaa: Haiiro risu no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.
Kyodai haiiro risu no kodomo no

Major: A large creature the shape of a gray squirrel.
Mejaa: Haiiro risu no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A person with the head and tail of a red squirrel.
Mejaa: Aka risu no atama to o wo motsu ningen da.
Kyodai aka risu no kodomo no

Major: A large creature the shape of a red squirrel.
Mejaa: Aka risu no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A tiny striped rodent found scurrying through the bushes and trees of the temperate forest.
Mejaa: Ontai no shigemi ya mori ni seisoku suru, shima moyou no chiisana geh harui da.

Major: A striped person with the head and tail of a chipmunk.
Mejaa: Shima risu no atama to o wo motsu, shima moyou no ningen da.
Kyodai Shima risu no kodomo no

Major: A large creature the shape of a chipmunk.
Mejaa: Shima risu no you na sugata wo shita kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small marine creature that lives in a shell rooted to the sea floor.
Mejaa: Kaitei ni haritsuku, kaisei no nimai kai da.

Major: A medium-Sized red fish that lives in the ocean and swims up a river to breed.
Mejaa: Umi kara kawa wo sojou shite sanran suru, chuugata no akai sakana da.

Major: A tiny orange marine fish that lives inside the tentacles of a poisonous invertebrate.
Mejaa: Iso ginchaku no naka ni sumu, orenji iro no chiisana kaisuigyo da.

Major: A small, spineless, eel-Like fish that lives on the bottom of the ocean.  It can turn the water around its body into a cloud of slime to escape predators.
Mejaa: Kaitei ni seisoku suru, toge no nai unagi no you na chiisana sakana. Karada no mawari no mizu wo suraimu no kumo ni kaete, hoshokusha kara nogareru koto ga dekimasu.

Major: Ability to tie themselves in knots
A small, jawless, filter-Feeding fish found in brooks and streams.
Mejaa: Ogawa ni sumu chiisana mugaku no roka sesshokugyo.

Major: A medium-Sized, winged fish found in the muddy coasts of both temperate and tropical waters.
Mejaa: Nettai no kisui ni sumu, chuugata no ei no nakama da.

Major: A small winged fish found in shallow seas.
Mejaa: Asai umi ni sumu, kogata no ei da.

Major: A small, shark-Like creature that lives in the ocean'S muddy shallows.  Its skin sparkles and it has a venomous spine on its back.
Mejaa: Asai umi ni sumu, chiisana same no you na ikimono. Kirakira kagayaku senaka ni, doku no toge wo motsu.

Major: A tiny marine fish found in vast schools.
Mejaa: Kyodai na mure wo tsukuru chiisana kaisuigyo.

Major: A small marine fish that travels to rivers to breed.
Mejaa: Sanran no tame ni kawa wo sojou suru, chiisana kaisuigyo.

Major: A tiny blue-Green oceanic fish, found only in temperate waters.
Mejaa: Nettai no umi ni seisoku suru, ao midoriiro no kozakana da.

Major: A medium-Sized fish found in tributaries and oceans.
Mejaa: Umi ya kawa ni seisoku suru chuugatagyo.

Major: A tiny, curved and colorful fish found in coral reefs.
Mejaa: Sango shou ni seisoku suru kawatta katachi no sakana da.

Major: A small, nocturnal, marine fish.  It can be found hunting in coral reefs.
Mejaa: Sango shou ni sumu yakousei no kozakana.

Major: A small flat fish found on the muddy bottom of shallow seas.
Mejaa: Asai umi ni sumu, hirabettai chiisana kaiteigyo da.

Major: A small flat fish found in the muddy bottom of coastal run-Offs and ponds.
Mejaa: Kinkai no soko ni seisoku suru, hirabettai kogatagyo da.

Major: A medium-Sized oceanic fish prized for its meat.
Mejaa: Gyoniku no kachi ga takai, chuugata kaisuigyo da.

Major: An invertebrate found off the coast.  It has a sting which can be severe.
Mejaa: Okiai ni sumu musekitsui doubutsu. Tsuyoi doku no shihou wo motsu.

Major: A tiny sea vermin with eight arms and two tentacles.  It can spray ink to confuse predators.
Mejaa: Hachipon no ude to nipon no shokushu wo motsu kaisei nantai doubutsu. Sumi wo haite hoshokusha no me wo kuramasu.

Major: A small person with a head bearing ten tentacles.
Mejaa: Ika no atama to juupon no shokushu wo motsu ningen da.

Major: A huge sea monster the shape of a squid.
Mejaa: Ika no you na sugata wo shita umi no kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A small fish which can walk on the land and breathe air.  It burrows in the mud when things get dry.
Mejaa: Riku wo aruite kuuki wo suu koto ga dekiru kozakana. Karada ga kawakuto doro no naka ni mogurikomimasu.

Major: A tiny orange-Striped fish.  It lives in inland waters.
Mejaa: Orenji iro no shima moyou no kogata tansuigyo.

Major: A small whiskered fish found in muddy inland waters.
A small whiskered fish found scavenging in inland waters.
Mejaa: Kitanai numa ni sumu chiisana namazu.

Major: A small whiskered fish found in inland waters.
A small spotted fish found in tropical rivers and lakes.
Mejaa: Nettai no kawa ya mizuumi ni sumu hanten no aru kogatagyo.

Major: A medium-Sized spotted fish found in temperate lakes and rivers.
Mejaa: Nettai no kawa ya mizuumi ni sumu hanten no aru chuugatagyo.

Major: A medium-Sized spotted fish found in temperate rivers and lakes.
Mejaa: Ontai no umi ya mizuumi ni sumu hanten no aru chuugatagyo.

Major: A tiny spotted fish found in coastal rivers and temperate lakes.
Mejaa: Ontai no umi ya mizuumi ni sumu hanten no aru kogatagyo.

Major: A small striped fish found in fresh water.
Mejaa: Kirei na mizu ni sumu, shima moyou no kogatagyo.

Major: A short, sturdy creature fond of drink and industry.
Mejaa: Sake to roudou ga daisuki na, joubu na kobito da.

Major: A medium-Sized creature prone to great ambition.
Mejaa: Ookina yashin wo idakiyasui chuugata no ikimono.

Major: A medium-Sized humanoid driven to cruelty by its evil nature.
Mejaa: Jaaku de zankoku na chuugata no ikimono.

Major: A small, squat humanoid with large pointy ears and yellow glowing eyes.
Mejaa: Ookina saki no togatta mimi to kiiro ni kagayaku me wo motsu chiisakute shaganda hitogata seibutsu.

Major: A small humanoid creature with a mischievous, toothy grin.
Mejaa: Itazurazuki de ha ga mukidashi na egao no chiisana hitogata seibutsu.

Major: A huge humanoid monster with coarse fur, large tusks and horns.
Mejaa: Arai kegawa, ookina kiba, kado wo motsu oogata no hitogata seibutsu da.

Major: A giant humanoid monster found stomping about in the evil plains.  Their low howls can be heard long before they are seen.
Mejaa: Jaaku na tochi ni sumu kyodai na hitogata seibutsu da. Yatsura ga arawareru mae ni wa, sono hoegoe ga kikoeru.

Major: A horse-Like creature with a spiral horn growing from its forehead.
Mejaa: Gaku kara rasenjou no kado ga haete iru uma no you na ikimono.

Major: A gigantic reptilian creature.  It is magical and can breathe fire.  These monsters can live for thousands of years.
Mejaa: Kyodai na hachuurui da. Mahou seibutsu de, hi wo haku koto ga deki, nanzen nen mo ikiru.

Major: A medium-Sized humanoid with the horns and legs of a goat.
Mejaa: Yagi no kado to ashi wo motsu chuugata no hitogata seibutsu.

Major: A gigantic magic statue made of bronze and bent on mayhem.
Mejaa: Seidou de tsukurareta mahou no zou da. Kako no arasoi de hinmagatte iru.

Major: A gigantic creature resembling a human, almost unparalleled in size.
Mejaa: Hirui nai hodo ni kyodai na hitogata seibutsu da.

Major: A giant humanoid monster with a single eye set in its forehead.
Mejaa: Tangan no kyodai na hitogata seibutsu da.

Major: A giant humanoid monster with two heads.
Mejaa: Futatsu no atama wo motsu oogata no hitogata kaibutsu da.

Major: A giant humanoid monster with the head of a bull.
Mejaa: Ushi no atama wo motta oogata hitogata kaibutsu.

Major: A large ape-Like creature with white fur, found in the snowy wilds.
Mejaa: Setsugen ni sumu, oogatarui jin'en da. Shiroi kegawa wo motsu.

Major: A large and mysterious ape-Like creature found in temperate forests.
Mejaa: Ontai no mori ni sumu, shinpiteki na oogatarui jin'en.

Major: A large humanoid monster from the wild tundra.  It has translucent skin, icicles for teeth, red glowing eyes and pointed ears.
Mejaa: Tsundora ni sumu oogata hitogata kaibutsu. Han toumei no hada, tsurara de dekita ha, akaku hikaru me, togatta mimi wo motsu.

Major: A fierce creature from the evil snowy wilds.  It has white fur and a piercing howl.
Mejaa: Jaaku na setsugen ni sumu seibutsu da. Shiroi kegawa to surudoi tooboe wo motsu.

Major: A tiny, giggling humanoid with lacy wings.
Mejaa: Reesu no hane wo motsu, kusukusu warau chiisana hitogata seibutsu.

Major: A creature from the evil swamp.  It resembles a squat, wingless bird with powerful beak and legs.  Its blotchy skin is brightly colored.
Mejaa: Jaaku na numachi ni seisoku suru. Kyouryoku na kuchibashi to ashi wo sonaeta, yotsuashi no tsubasa no nai tori ni nite iru. Sono shimi no aru hada wa azayaka na iro desu.

Major: An evil monster from the swamp.  It resembles a knot of waterlogged weeds but will strike the unaware victim.
Mejaa: Numa ni hisomu jaaku na kaibutsu. Mizubitashi no zassou ni gitai shi, kizukanai giseisha wo osou.

Major: A man-Shaped creature with the legs of a goat and the empty-Eyed skull of a goat.
Mejaa: Yagi no zugaikotsu ga sono mama atama ni natta, yagi no ashi wo motsu hitogata no ikimono da.

Major: A large, four-Armed ape creature with three eyes and razor-Sharp teeth.
Mejaa: Yonpon no ude ni mittsume, kamisori no you na ha wo motsu oogatarui jin'en da.

Major: A flying monster with stretched skin over its emaciated body.  It has the head of a jackal with needle-Like horns protruding through its mane.
Mejaa: Tategami no aru jakkaru no atama kara hari no you na kado ga tsukideta, yasekoketa koumori no you na tsubasa no aru hitogata kaibutsu da.

Major: A monster in the shape of a woman with a bird'S wings in place of arms and talons for feet.
Mejaa: Ude no kawari ni tori no hane wo motsu, josei no katachi wo shita kaibutsu da.

Major: A giant dragon-Like monster with seven biting heads.
Mejaa: Nanatsu no atama wo motsu, doragon no you na kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A man-Like creature with the tail of a fish instead of legs.
Mejaa: Ashi no kawari ni sakana no obire wo motsu, ningen no you na kaibutsu da.

Major: A giant limbless dragon that lives in the sea.
Mejaa: Umi ni sumu doragon no you na, kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A giant creature with many eyes and arms to terrify the sea.
Mejaa: Umi ni sumu, takusan no me to ude wo motta osoroshii kyodai na kaibutsu da.

Major: A bird of prey so large and ferocious it dwarfs many dragons.  All beneath its mighty wings should fear the sky.
Mejaa: Doragon sura chiisaku kanjirareru hodo no ookisa no moukinrui da. Sono tsubasa no shita ni iru ikimono wa, amaneku kyoufu ni osowarerudarou.

Major: A huge, predatory reptile with pale, colorless scales and red eyes.  It lives in caves and ambushes its prey.
Mejaa: Awai mushoku no uroko to akai me wo motsu kyodai nikushoku hachuurui. Doukutsu ni sumi, emono wo machibuse shimasu.

Major: A giant amphibian predator found underground.
Mejaa: Chika ni seisoku suru oogata ryouseirui.

Major: A giant amphibian predator found underground near water.
Mejaa: Chika no mizube ni seisoku suru oogata ryouseirui da.

Major: A giant flying mammal found underground.
Mejaa: Chika ni seisoku suru sora tobu oogata honyuurui.
Chika ni seisoku suru oogatage pparui.

Major: A large, pale rodent with loose, hanging, hairless skin.  It has long teeth and an incredibly powerful bite.  It is found underground.
Mejaa: Ookina gesshi doubutsu de, usukute mumou no hifu ga taresagatte iru. Sore wa nagai ha to kyouryoku na ago wo motsu. Chika ni seisoku suru.
Doukutsu ni sumu yaban na hitogata seibutsu.

Major: A gigantic digging creature found underground.
Mejaa: Chika ni sumu ana wo horisusumu kyodai seibutsu.

Major: A small humanoid surrounded by fire which they can hurl at their enemies.
Mejaa: Honoo ni oowareta chiisana hitogata seibutsu da. Sono honoo wo teki ni nagetsukeru koto ga dekiru.

Major: A large underground monster with eight legs and sharp, venomous fangs.
Mejaa: Surudoi dokuga ni hachipon no ashi wo motsu, chika ni sumu no kyodai na kumo da.
Kootta kyodai doukutsu kumo no dokueki
Joukika shita kyodai doukutsu kumo no dokueki

Major: A tiny underground bug, sought after for its thread.
Mejaa: Shiri kara ito wo dasu chiisana chika ni sumu mushi da.
Joukika shita doukutsu kumo no dokueki

Major: A small pale creature found in underground streams and ponds.
Mejaa: Chika no kawa ya mizuumi ni sumu, aojiroi kozakana da.

Major: A humanoid creature with the head of a blind cave fish.  They live in colonies in watery regions far underground.
Mejaa: Doukutsugyo no atama wo motta hitogata seibutsu da. Chika shinbu de mure wo tsukuru.

Major: A small, pale arthropod found in underground streams and ponds.
Mejaa: Chika no kawa ya mizuumi ni sumu, aojiroi kogata sessoku doubutsu da.

Major: A serpent made of pure fire which can inject liquid fire as venom.
Mejaa: Ekitai no hi wo doku to shite chuunyuu dekiru, junsui na hi de tsukurareta hebi.

Major: An animal person with the head of the amphibious olm.  It lives underground near water.
Mejaa: Hora imori no atama wo motta ningen da. Chika no mizube ni sumu.

Major: A tiny winged creature that hunts at night and rests in caves during the day.
Mejaa: Yoru ni kari wo shi, nitchuu wa doukutsu de yasumu, tsubasa no aru kogata seibutsu.

Major: A humanoid with the head of a bat and wings stretching from wrist to ankle.

Major: A tiny larva which is prized for its milk.
Mejaa: Chiisana imomushi. Miruku no kachi ga takai.

Major: Fire in the shape of a human that can hurl fireballs.
Mejaa: Hito no katachi wo shita honoo da. Kakyuu wo nagetsukete kuru.

Major: Magma moving in the shape of a man.  It has a cracked black crust.
Mejaa: Hito no katachi wo shita maguma da. Hibi no haitta kuroi kaku wo motsu.

Major: A man-Shaped creature made of iron.
Mejaa: Hitogata no tetsu de dekita ikimono da. Naibu ga kuudou de, yuudoku gasu ga tamatte iru.

Major: A humanoid made of mud which lives near water underground.
Mejaa: Chika no mizube ni sumu,nin no katachi no doro da.

Major: A small blue and orange bird.
Mejaa: Ao to orenji no chiisana tori da.

Major: A feathered man with the wings and head of a bird.  It lives underground.
Mejaa: Doukutsu tsubame no atama to tsubasa wo motsu, umou no haeta ningen da.

Major: A gigantic blue and orange bird.
Mejaa: Ao to orenji no kyodai na tori da.
Kyodai doukutsu tsubame no kodomo no

Major: These evil creatures resemble walking frogs with arms and the intelligence to use them.  They live in the waters far under the earth.
Mejaa: Ude no haeta kaeru ni nita jaaku na ikimono da. Chika shinbu no mizu ni seisoku suru.

Major: These creatures are shaped like men covered with rough scales.  They have the head and tail of a lizard and possess a dark and evil intelligence.  They are found deep under the earth.
Mejaa: Tokage no atama wo o wo motsu jaaku na ishi wo sonaeta ningen da. Chika shinbu ni sumu.

Major: A large white snake with the arms and torso of a man.  These creatures are evil and live far underground.

Joukika shita hebi otoko no dokueki
